f(x)=2x^3-5x^2=kx-20
 \begin{align} f(x) & = 2x^3 - 5x^2 = kx - 20 \\ \\ & = 2x^3 - 5x^2 - kx + 20 = 0 \tag{1}\\ \\ &= (x+2)(2x^2 -9x + 10)=0\tag{2}\\ \\ \end{align}  
(-18 +10)x = -kx \implies k = 8.
